interfaces.dataStructures.stack
Interface Stack<E>

public interface Stack<E>

A stack is a First In Last Out (FILO) data-structure. Items can either be pushed onto the stack, popped off the stack, or examined using peek. A stack can not be iteratively traversed.

Author:
w_jossey
